text: Oh my, so horrible. They were nice at 1st when I dropped my truck off 2b sold. They claimed it would sell quick becuz of the price I gave them which was $1500. It sat there for 2months and the person that actually wanted to buy it for $1500 didn't because they had changed the price to try and get more money that I'm sure they wanted to keep for themselves. 3rd degree Crooks you asked me😒

name: Jay Q
text: I visited this dealer and decided to purchase an impala. Two and a half miles after leaving this lot the vehicle ran hot and then completely died. There was absolutely no oil in it and no water in the radiator. After putting oil in it, immediately I noticed the oil was leaking out. I did test drive before I bought it but the dealer told me that since it didn't have gas in it that I should only go up the block and back. THAT SHOULD'VE BEEN A RED FLAG! They made sure the was no fluids in it to avoid buyers noticing leaks at the lot and no gas to ensure a potential buyer couldn't test drive it long enough for it to run hot. Even though they did give my money back, I had to pay for a tow truck and go through this ordeal. THIS PLACE SCAMS BUYERS! Never again will I patron this place!

name: Simply Carter (Simply Carter)
text: I am an employee here and have been since Dec 2016. The staff are great, always willing to answer questions that current and new dealers have. Multiple staff members that divide and conquer the yard assisting dealers and sellers with business. Available options of picking up and delivering vehicles across a wide radius range, auto detailing, and inspection of every vehicle entered. Can't get a car, come back next week, auctions are held every Wednesday. Couldn't win the highest bed on a car, ask our staff members about "IF Deals". Just because you didn't get the highest bid doesn't mean you can't leave with the vehicle. Great staff friendly family atmosphere. Come in and check us out for yourself!

resp.text: Thank you for taking time to leave us feedback!  While we do make every attempt to follow the order of the printed catalog, it is sometimes necessary to deviate based on the item location and the amount of space we have to work with at each sale.  Our auctioneer will always announce the item number and description prior to selling each item. Your business is greatly appreciated and we look forward to seeing you at future auctions.  Sincerely, Beau Cole
